{{Infobox Politician | honorific-prefix = [[Honourable]] | name = Ameen Faisal | image = | imagesize = | caption = | birth_date =January 16, 1963 | birth_place = | residence = | death_date = | death_place = | office = National Security Advisor | term_start = 10 December 2010 | to Present | predecessor = [[Mohamed Zahir]] | successor = | constituency = | office2 = Minister of Defense and National Security | term_start2 = 12 November 2008 | term_end2 = 10 December 2010 | predecessor2 = | successor2 = [[Mohamed Nasheed#Presidential Cabinet|Mohamed Muizzu Adnan]] ''(Acting)'' | constituency2 = | party = [[Maldives Democratic Party]] | religion = Muslim | occupation = | relations = | spouse = Aminath Mubarik | children = 4 children | website = | footnotes = }} '''Ameen Faisal''' is the current National Security Advisor<ref>{{Cite web |url=http://www.haveeru.com.mv/english/details/33780/President_appoints_Ameen_Faisal_as_National_Security_Advisor |title=Archived copy |access-date=2010-12-20 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20101213165743/http://www.haveeru.com.mv/english/details/33780/President_appoints_Ameen_Faisal_as_National_Security_Advisor |archive-date=2010-12-13 |dead-url=yes |df= }}</ref> and former [[Minister of Defence]] and National Security of the [[Republic of Maldives]].<ref>{{cite news |title=Maldivian Defence Minister in Belgaum |url=http://www.hindu.com/2009/10/30/stories/2009103052500300.htm |work=[[The Hindu]] |date=30 October 2009 |accessdate=5 December 2010 }}</ref>
He is currently married to Aminath Mubarik. He has four children. He is the grandson of the first president of Maldives, [[Mohamed Ameen Didi]]. Faisal was born to the only daughter of [[Mohamed Ameen Didi|Ameen Didi]], Ameena Ameen. His father is Abdul Majeed Mahir. Faisal currently lives in Male', Maldives after living in Sri Lanka for over four years with his family.
